{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"USN-7472-1","published":"2025-05-01T13:04:26.449311Z","modified":"2025-10-13T04:41:07Z","related":["UBUNTU-CVE-2021-42553","UBUNTU-CVE-2024-8946","UBUNTU-CVE-2024-8947"],"upstream":["CVE-2021-42553","CVE-2024-8946","CVE-2024-8947","UBUNTU-CVE-2021-42553","UBUNTU-CVE-2024-8946","UBUNTU-CVE-2024-8947"],"summary":"micropython vulnerabilities","details":"Junwha Hong and Wonil Jang discovered that Micropython incorrectly handled\nthe length of a buffer in mp_vfs_umount, leading to a heap-based buffer \noverflow vulnerability. If a user or automated system were tricked into\nopening a specially crafted file, an attacker could possibly use this issue\nto cause a denial of service or possibly execute arbitrary code.\n(CVE-2024-8946)\n\n\nJunwha Hong and Wonil Jang discovered that Micropython incorrectly handled\nmemory, leading to a use-after-free vulnerability under certain \ncircumstances. If a user or automated system were tricked into opening a \nspecially crafted file, an attacker could possibly use this issue to\ncause a denial of service or possibly execute arbitrary code. \n(CVE-2024-8947)\n\nIt was discovered that Middleware USB Host MCU Component incorrectly\nhandled memory, leading to a buffer overflow vulnerability, If a user or \nautomated system were tricked into opening a specially crafted file, an \nattacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service or\npossibly execute arbitrary code. (CVE-2021-42553)\n","affected":[{"package":{"name":"micropython","ecosystem":"Ubuntu:Pro:20.04:LTS","purl":"pkg:deb/ubuntu/micropython@1.12-1ubuntu0.1~esm1?arch=source&distro=esm-apps/focal"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.12-1ubuntu0.1~esm1"}]}],"versions":["1.12-1"],"ecosystem_specific":{"availability":"Available with Ubuntu Pro: https://ubuntu.com/pro","binaries":[{"binary_name":"micropython","binary_version":"1.12-1ubuntu0.1~esm1"}]},"database_specific":{"cves_map":{"cves":[{"id":"CVE-